CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1944, p. 13, reads: "PITTSBURGH HONORS LENA HORNE - After her socko performance in Pittsburgh, Lena is shown at the station with her father, Teddy Horne (left) and her accompanist, Horace Henderson, as they entrained for Chicago ... then to Hollywood."
TitMainTitle: Teddy Horne, Lena Horne, and Horace Henderson holding telephone, posed in Pittsburgh train station
